  <glossary>
    <definition id="import-auto-id1012671"><term>resistivity</term> <meaning id="fs-id3082005">an intrinsic property of a material, independent of its shape or size, directly proportional to the resistance, denoted by <emphasis effect="italics">ρ</emphasis></meaning></definition>
    <definition id="import-auto-id3305400"><term>temperature coefficient of resistivity</term> <meaning id="fs-id2448387">an empirical quantity, denoted by <emphasis effect="italics">α</emphasis>, which describes the change in resistance or resistivity of a material with temperature</meaning></definition>
  </glossary>
